Setting the date of birth is important to aid the navigation and the different computations. You can do this from Prefrences/Baby settings or by tapping the main page left icon and going directly to Baby settings. You can also introduce here your baby's picture by pressing the picture square
column2: so you have your baby's image as the icon in the app title bar.  Main page  Start using the app by pressing one of the action buttons bellow the title
column3: in the page top bar. Below there is the date navigator
column4: the next and previous day buttons and
column5: on the right
column6: the calendar allowing you to pick any date. Bellow the navigator
column7: there is a list with all the actions recorded in the active day: time
column8: title and description.  Common actions functionality For each action
column9: you can set the date and time
column10: by tapping the blue rectangles from the top of the page: first rectangle for time
column11: and second for date. Also
column12: you can add notes (e.g. Took the vitamin
column13: but spat out most of it). Two buttons are placed on the bottom of the page: Cancel - to abort current action and Save & Exit - to add the action and go back to main page. Each action is optimized to work both vertically and horizontally. For Nursing and Sleep actions
column14: changing page orientation is not possible.  Persistence functionality For actions involving a timer (sleep and breast feeding)
column17: allowing you to leave the action page or even the app while the counter goes on. The action button flashes to signal a persistent action.  Edit & Delete an action By long pressing an item from the daily list (main page)
column18: you can choose to edit or delete an existing recorded action.  Actions functionality   [[bottle]] Bottle feeding  You can change the measuring unit between oz and ml. After change
column19: the max and current values will be changed accordingly. After Mom milk is checked
column20: you can slide the bar to select a value between 0 and maximum. Also
column21: you can change the max value by tapping the blue box on the right. The same functionality for Formula milk.   [[nurse]] Breast feeding  On top
column23: you have an info box about the last used breast. It indicates the breast you used in the previous action
column24: not now. Two big blue boxes come next
column25: one marked left and one right. By tapping the play button accordingly you'll start recording the feeding time
column26: and the box becomes green. Tapping play on the other box automatically stops the previous one. Also
column27: you can manually change the time by tapping in the blue box
column28: but outside the play/pause button. The button bellow is a general stop
column29: stopping both timers.   [[diaper]] Changing diapers  You can select if there was a pee or not
column30: if there was a poop or not
column31: and three degrees of pooping.   [[sleep]] Sleeping  Like in Breast feeding you have a big blue box for counting the sleeping time. The sleeping time can also be changed manually.   [[med]] Take medicine  By using the Medicine selector you can choose which medicine to record. Using the button Edit medicine list
column33: modify or delete every medicine to/from the list. Each line is a medicine.   [[bath]] Bath time!  Nothing specific here.   [[gener]] Generic action  You can introduce here new actions you find useful to track in relation to your baby. As in Take medicine
column34: you have a selector to see an action name
column35: and a button Edit title list to manage the generic actions list.   [[solid]] Solid food  Very similar in functionality with "Take medicine" action. You can also rate how much the baby likes a food.   [[pump]] Breast pumping  It allows you to record the quantity of breast milk you pumped. There are separate measurements for each breast. Also
column36: you can set the last breast you pumped. You can change the measuring unit between oz and ml.    [[meas]] Measuring  You are able now to measure and check the progress for length
column37: weight and head circumference of your baby. You can change the measuring unit between cm/kg and inches/pounds.     [[stat]] Statistics  You can follow your baby's progress by going to the statistics
column38: the first button after the action ones in the action bar. You can choose between seven types of statistics: daily digest
column43: sleep progress and last event (telling you how much time has lapsed since the last action in each category). In daily digest page
column44: you can go to a specific day by long tapping the corresponding list element. In the last action page
column45: you will see just the actions you selected to be used in actions bar. In bottle progress page
column46: you have the graph of quantities in magenta and a graph of average values in gray.    [[gstat]] Growth Statistics  Similar with statistics.  Shacking gesture You can configure a shortcut for the last event statistics
column47: accessible by shacking the phone/tablet.  App Help Each page has a question mark icon on the right of the title bar. When you first tap it you'll have to choose between local help and online help. After that
column48: it always will open the one you first selected. If you want to change the selection
column49: long tap the question mark icon.  Action bar customization By long tapping an action in the action bar
column50: you can change the visibility and place for each action.  Export feature You can also export data. From the main window
column51: you can export the current day by tapping the export button from the title. In the statistics window you will also find an export button for daily digest and for bottle progress.  Last event widget You have the possibility to add this important information to your main page. You can have maximum 6 last actions. They will appear in the same order as in the action bar.  Sync functionality You can auto synchronize (via net) the log between many devices. The action can be activated from the drawer.    [[alert]] Alerts & Notifications  There is the possibility to add
column53: four types of notifications or alerts: fixed time
column56: action count overall. For each event you can add sound
column57: flash signals or vibrations.) (LOC Bottom) <SEP> (TYPE android.widget.ScrollView) (TEXT ) (LOC Bottom) <SEP> (TYPE android.widget.LinearLayout) (TEXT ) (LOC Bottom) <SEP> (TYPE android.widget.Button) (TEXT Close) (LOC Bottom right) <SEP>

column257: and Ireland. Any personal or other information contained in email will be stored in a data centre in one or more of those countries.  Any overseas disclosure does not affect our commitment to safeguarding your personal or other information. Where reasonable in the circumstances

column265: modification and disclosure. Such steps include: physical security over paper-based and electronic data storage and premises; computer and network security measures
column267: password access and secure servers; restricting access to your personal information to employees and those acting on our behalf who are authorised and on a 'need to know' basis; retaining your personal information for no longer than it is reasonably required
column268: unless we are required by law to retain it for longer; and entering into confidentiality agreements with staff and third parties.  Allhomes uses a hosting provider for the storage of its information. The hosting provider uses a primary server room in Canberra and a secondary server room in Sydney. From May 2014
column269: allhomes’ hosting provider’s primary server room will be in Sydney and its secondary server room will be in Hong Kong. Secure access to physical servers is controlled by allhomes’ hosting provider. Access to the information stored on the servers is protected by username/password authentication authorisation schemes.  Data transmissions between allhomes’ servers and its hosting provider’s servers is encrypted using Secure Sockets Layer ("SSL") security mechanisms.  Allhomes uses network vulnerability testers to ensure the security of its data. Allhomes also uses monitoring devices within its network infrastructure to notify of incursion or attempted incursion. The inner promptings you receive are often your angel leading you to where you should be going in life. However
column2: it’s up to you to choose whether or not to listen to what he or she is saying. Your guardian angel has a name so that you can call upon him or her at any time. If you don’t already know what your guardian angel’s name is
column3: there’s a very simple way to find that information out.  All you need to do is set aside a few minutes and find a quiet place where you will not be disturbed.  Sit in a comfortable seat where you can sit up straight and place your feet flat on the floor. Make sure to take off anything that binds you
column4: including jewelry
column5: shoes
column6: or a tight belt. Just sit there a few minutes and relax. Then take a nice deep breath
column7: and let it out like a sigh of relief. As you inhale
column8: imagine yourself taking in everything that you want. As you exhale
column9: imagine yourself letting go of anything that you don’t want. Now begin to count just your inhales. When you reach the number twenty
column10: simply ask your guardian angel his or her name. Then quiet your thoughts and wait for an answer. Be patient and know that your response is coming. The answer may come as a thought
column11: a picture
column13: or even an audible voice. Be open to accept whatever is given to you. If at first you don’t receive anything
column14: ask your guardian angel to speak louder so that you can hear him or her. The most common way to receive an answer is as a thought
column15: so if a name just pops in your head
column16: don’t think you are making it up. In this case
column17: your guardian angel is speaking to you telepathically
column18: so make sure to accept whatever you are you are receiving. The key is to simply listen for the first name that comes to you. Your guardian angel is yours alone so don’t try to look it up to see if there is such an angel. So if the name seems funny to you
column19: accept it anyway. If you have doubts about what you have received
column20: ask your angel to confirm the name by giving you signs during the next few days with his or her name in it. For example
column21: if you were given the name Rebecca
column22: and start seeing that name on billboards
column26: know that you have truly received the correct name. Your guardian angel wants you to know his or her name and will gladly give you the confirmation you need!Remember
column27: all you have to do is ask

column3: which hastens the proofing of the dough. I simply turn my oven to WARM for a few minutes
column4: then shut it off. Dissolve the yeast in warm water and the sugar until it foams (5-10 minutes). In the meantime
column5: melt the butter in the microwave
column6: then the milk. Combine and allow to cool to about 110F. (You could use a saucepan
column7: but the microwave is much easier for me-- I use 25 second increments.) Dump the milk and yeast mixture into the mixing bowl. Add about 2-1/2 cups flour and mix with the dough hook. (Or
column8: beat by hand). Mix for about a minute. With the mixer still going
column9: add the remaining flour
column10: a bit at a time and mix for another couple of minutes
column11: or until the dough starts to clean the sides of the bowl. (I used 3 cups of flour
column12: total). Knead on low speed for about 2 more minutes
column13: or until dough is smooth and elastic – the dough will still be slightly sticky to the touch. Place dough in a lightly oiled bowl
column14: turning it to grease the top. Cover the dough with a clean
column16: (or plastic wrap) and let it rise in a warm place
column17: free from draft (or in the incubated oven)
column18: for about 20 minutes. Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface
column19: and gently shape into a square. Divide into 9 or 12 pieces. I shape each roll by pulling them into a more circular shape then grab corners to the center and twist. Place the ball on a lightly floured surface
column20: twist side down and gently grab and roll into a round ball. You can also make 27 or 24 small balls and make "clover leaf rolls". You then place3 mini dough balls into a greased muffin cup. Cover the rolls with the dish towel
column21: and let the dough rise for about 15 minutes. Meanwhile
column22: preheat the oven for 425ºF. Bake for about 12 minutes or until the rolls are golden brown. Remove from pans immediately
column23: and brush with 2 Tablespoons melted butter
column24: immediately. Cool on a wire rack
column25: and you can eat these within just a few minutes. The texture of these rolls are fluffy and this is now my "go to" recipe for bread rolls.) column2: Rechild What is new: -v2.2.1B216 resize widget  -v2.2.0B215 remove 'menu'and 'check' button apply new UI  -v2.1.3B213 Roll back to old widget size  -v2.1.2B212 Fix "cannot get process issue" for Android 5.0 and later version Fix widget icon. Change UI to old version.  *New feature*  1. What is the 'Check' button? This is used to check if your phone has any issues. Since this is a new feature
column3: we don't have many checking items yet. You can use it to check if your phone has any apps pushing ads.  *General help*  1. How to use it (for new users to quick start)? It is pretty simple. Open this tool and take a look at the running applications list? Uncheck some apps you don't want to kill (such as Advanced Task Killer and some system apps) Tap the button 'Kill selected apps'
column4: it will kill all applications checked.  2. How to use it (for new users to do more)? If you don't want to kill any application
column5: you can tap it on the running applications list. Then it's checking box will turn to gray.      3. Why there are programs running that I haven't used or even opened? Some applications will start up once you turn on your phone or be invoked by some events.  4. What is ignore list/ignore? Ignore list is for you to ignore some applications you don't want to kill. If you long press on the application listed on the main screen of ATK
column6: the menu will pop up
column7: then you can select 'Ignore'
column8: the application would be moved to ignore list. When you tap 'Kill selected apps'
column9: it won't be killed any more.  5. What is default action for long press You can set your default action for long press and click on the settings. The system default action for long press is pop-menu. That means you when you long press on the application(displays on the running applications list)
column10: a pop-menu would shows up. For example
column11: if you want to switch to the application after you long press on it
column12: you can set the default action of long press to 'Switch to'.   6. What is Auto-Kill We don't suggest people use auto kill. Abusing auto kill might consume more resources. If you want to kill apps automatically you need to choose one of auto-kill level 1. Safe: Only kill the apps aren't running but still consume memory. 2. Aggressive: Kill the apps running background and apps aren't running. 3. Crazy: All apps except for apps you are using with. You should be able to see Auto Kill information shows on the title
column13: like 'Auto-Kill: 12:20'. That means auto kill will start at 12:20
column14: you can also change the frequency to impact the auto kill start time. If you encounter any issues in security level low
column15: you can kill them one by one to find out which one cuase these issues
column16: then you can uncheck or ignore it.  7. What is Security Level We suggest people keep it as 'High'. Changing security level might cause some issues
column17: if you don't know your phone well.  You can set it to low to show more apps
column18: but you need know more about the apps to decide which one you need to ignore.   8. Why I have some green items on running list? Those apps are services and front apps. identity of the Reddit user who made an anti-CNN
column2: Trump-themed GIF if he reneged on an apology – but some critics suggested the network also could have a legal problem on its hands.  Republican Texas Sen. Ted Cruz took to Twitter to cite Georgia state law’s prohibition against “theft by extortion.”  “Troubling. I assume CNN's lawyers are examining GA § 16-8-16 Theft by extortion. If CNN constructively obtained the gif-maker's IP...it's a GA crime if they threatened to ‘Disseminate any information tending to subject any person to hatred
column3: contempt
column4: or ridicule....’” he wrote
column5: citing a portion of the statute.  WikiLeaks’ Julian Assange also claimed on Twitter that CNN may have violated various state and federal laws related to “coercion” and the First Amendment.  CNN
column6: however
column7: has adamantly defended its handling of the story
column8: issuing a statement Wednesday saying the network did not publish the user’s name out of concern for his safety -- adding
column9: "Any assertion that the network blackmailed or coerced him is false."   In the statement
column10: CNN said the team published the line in question to be “transparent that there was no deal.”  Andrew Kaczynski
column11: the senior editor and founding member of the cable network's KFile investigative team
column12: tweeted several defenses of the article
column13: saying parts were “being misinterpreted.”  Related Image   Expand / Collapse  Andrew Kaczynski is a senior editor and founding member of CNN's KFile investigative team.  The Reddit user in question was behind the controversial GIF that President Trump tweeted out Sunday -- and that showed Trump wrestling an opponent (from his pre-politician days) with a CNN logo plastered over his face. The KFile group found the creator -- user name “HanA**holeSolo” -- by comparing information posted on Reddit to Facebook profiles. While CNN decided against publishing the user's real name
column14: the network appeared to attach a caveat to that decision.  “CNN is not publishing ‘HanA**holeSolo’s’ name because he is a private citizen who has issued an extensive statement of apology
column15: showed his remorse by saying he has taken down all his offending posts
column16: and because he said he is not going to repeat this ugly behavior on social media again

Earhart, who was attempting to fly around the world, disappeared on July 2, 1937 during a flight from Papua New Guinea to Howland Island in the Pacific. Researchers claim that new evidence from U.S. Government archives may finally solve the mystery of what happened to the record-breaking pilot.  A two-hour documentary “Amelia Earhart: The Lost Evidence” will reveal the documents when it airs on the History channel July 9.  Investigators will present the theory that Earhart survived her final flight after crash-landing in the Marshall Islands. The aviator, they say, was then captured by the Japanese military and died in their custody on the island of Saipan. The investigators also claim that the U.S. government may have covered up Earhart’s fate, citing the possibility that she was on a spying mission.  NEW SEARCH WILL LOOK FOR AMELIA EARHART’S BONES  The Japanese government has not yet responded to a request for comment on this story from Fox News.  Related Image   Expand / Collapse  A closeup of the image (Photograph courtesy of Les Kinney/U.S. National Archives)  A photograph, which purportedly shows Earhart, her navigator Fred Noonan and their ill-fated plane after the crash, is presented as a critical piece of evidence in the documentary. The photo was found within the U.S. National Archives by Les Kinney, a former U.S. Treasury Agent. “The photograph came out of a Navy file, a formerly top secret file in the National Archives,” says Kinney, during the documentary. “It was misfiled and that was the only reason I found it.”  The photo of a group of people on a Marshall Islands dock shows Earhart sitting with her back to the camera, according to Kinney. “Look at the body, the build, the short hair, the fact that she’s Caucasian,” he explained, adding that the tall man on the left of the group is Noonan.  NEW EVIDENCE REPORTEDLY INDICATES AMELIA EARHART SURVIVED CRASH  Earhart’s plane is said to be on a barge in the far right of the picture, which was tested with recognition and proportional comparison technology.  Related Image   Expand / Collapse  A closeup of the image - researchers say that the man on the left is Fred Noonan (Photograph courtesy of Les Kinney/U.S. National Archives)  The documentary also focuses on plane parts found on Mili Atoll in the Marshall Islands that are said to be consistent with the aircraft Earhart was flying in 1937.  However, Dorothy Cochrane, curator in the Aeronautics department of the Smithsonian National Air and Space Museum told Fox News there is no evidence that Earhart was sent out on a spying mission. Cochrane, who has not yet seen the new documentary says that unravelling the Earhart mystery remains incredibly difficult. “There’s no definite evidence that anyone has got as to where she ended up,” she said.  The first woman to fly solo across the Atlantic Ocean, Earhart was one of the most famous people at the time of her disappearance. A number of theories have emerged about her fate.  AMELIA EARHART'S PLANE DISCOVERED ... IN OLD MOVIE  One theory is that Earhart died a castaway after landing her plane on the remote island of Nikumaroro, a coral atoll some 1,200 miles from the Marshall Islands.  Some 13 human bones were found on Nikumaroro, which is also known as Gardner Island, three years after Earhart’s disappearance. The bones, however, were subsequently lost.  A new search for other bones on the island was recently launched.  The Associated Press contributed to this article. column95: a challenge that officials say they are ill-equipped to address.  There are at least 180 cross-border tunnels and intricate drainage systems between Mexico and California and Arizona

column99: use these tunnels to move drugs and illegally smuggle people across the border largely undetected. As the number of tunnels grow and become more sophisticated
column100: Border Patrol agents say they are falling behind in finding technology that will detect them.  MEXICO'S UNFILLED BORDER TUNNELS A SECURITY RISK
column102: a member of the Border Patrol elite tunnel team working out of the San Diego Sector
column103: said his team of five agents patrol the daunting miles of storm drains that lead them to connecting tunnels along the border.   slideshow  “They are always digging tunnels somewhere
column104:
Lenoir said.  Scott Stewart, vice president of tactical analysis for Stratfor, a geopolitical intelligence firm based out of Austin, Texas, said Mexican drug dealers are shelling out millions of dollars to build underground tunnels into the U.S. And very few people, he said, know about their existence. Some of these tunnels have rail systems, lighting, ventilation and hydraulic lifts.  UNEARTHED: 2 TUNNELS LEADING INTO CALIFORNIA FROM MEXICO FOUND  “In order to ensure a good return on this huge investment, the cartel groups work to keep the tunnel’s existence and the locations of its exits a secret,” Stewart said. “In fact, we have seen cases in which cartels have brought laborers in to dig tunnels and then killed them after they were done to keep the tunnel secret.”  He said those who do know about the tunnel are highly trusted employees and “very few in numbers to ensure solid operational security.”  The tunnels that are discovered are usually found by Border Patrol tunnel specialists or by accident during narcotics surveillance operations.  One recent tunnel discovered in October 2016 ran 330 yards from an ice store near the Tijuana airport to a store just across the border in the U.S. Officials said about 5 tons of marijuana was found in the tunnel and in the buildings on both sides of the border. The tunnels were found because of an anonymous tip – not because of detecting equipment, Lenoir said.  Lenoir said technology, such as ground-penetrating radar, does exist. But not only is it ineffective in many areas along the border, it is not available to enough agents to make a major impact.  And criminals are exploiting the weaknesses in detection technology.  “Unfortunately, we are severely lacking in technology,” he said, referring to the number of field agents available and the quality of the existing equipment to reliably detect a tunnel. “It’s difficult trying to find something in a specific geologic region that is in a confined space that can be 4 feet in diameter and 90 feet underground.”  Limiting the available technology: Surface noise. The noise from nearby traffic and major freeways and unregulated radio traffic from Mexico impairs an agent’s ability to detect what’s happening below ground.  “We’re aggressively pursuing better technology and interdiction strategies,” Lenoir said, “but it also has to come down to political will.”  Joseph J. column108: services and websites.  What we collect and how is it used?  We collect anonymous analytics to help us better understand how our audience uses our products. This includes information about the User's device such as operating system version
column111: coarse location and usage information of our game. We don't collect any personal information for analytics. The purpose of analytics is to be able to continuously improve our products and the experience for our users. We retain the right to collect and store identifying information for the sole purpose of providing user accounts to improve the quality
column112: features and user experience of our products. All identifying information will be stored and handled with proper security measures.  Third Party services (Advertisements and Analytics)  We display advertisements in our free apps and games to fund the development process for current and future products. The advertisements are provided by third party companies and they may use and collect anonymous data about the user's interests to be able to select more relevant advertisements. This information may also include location data and unique device identifier. No information is collected to allow third parties identifying you as a person. We use an external tool for the collection of analytics information. The tool uses similar information as used with advertisements.  By pressing "Accept" you signify your acceptance of this policy.
